The paper deals with the query complexity of Bayesian Private Learning, which involves privacy, estimation, and learning. The paper uses techniques from information theory, machine learning, and cryptography. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
